# Playwright Best Practices

**APPLY WHEN:** Writing or reviewing Playwright end-to-end tests.

---

## 1. Use `@playwright/test` Runner

Use the official test runner for fixtures, isolation, and web-first assertions. Avoid the low-level `playwright` library for E2E tests.

**DO**:
```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';
test('should navigate to home', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/');
  await expect(page).toHaveTitle(/Home/);
});
```

**STOP**:
```typescript
import { chromium } from 'playwright';
const browser = await chromium.launch();
// Manual setup/teardown - use @playwright/test instead
```

---

## 2. Robust Locators

Prefer user-facing attributes over brittle CSS selectors.

**DO**:
```typescript
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Add to Cart' }).click();
await page.getByLabel('Username').fill('testuser');
await page.getByTestId('product-item-123').click();
```

**STOP**:
```typescript
await page.locator('div.container > ul > li:nth-child(2) > button').click();
```

---

## 3. Web-First Assertions

Use `expect()` assertions that auto-retry. Never use `page.waitForTimeout()`.

**DO**:
```typescript
await expect(page).toHaveTitle(/My Page/);
await expect(page.getByText('Welcome')).toBeVisible();
await expect(page.getByRole('checkbox')).toBeChecked();
```

**STOP**:
```typescript
await page.waitForTimeout(2000); // Flaky
const title = await page.title();
assert.equal(title, 'My Page'); // Not web-first
```

---

## 4. Page Object Model (POM)

Encapsulate selectors and actions in dedicated classes for reuse and maintainability.

**DO**:
```typescript
// pages/LoginPage.ts
export class LoginPage {
  constructor(readonly page: Page) {}
  async login(username: string, password: string) {
    await this.page.getByLabel('Username').fill(username);
    await this.page.getByLabel('Password').fill(password);
    await this.page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Login' }).click();
  }
}
```

---

## 5. Auth State and Route Blocking

Reuse authenticated sessions and block unnecessary resources for faster tests.

**DO**:
- Use `storageState` in config for saved auth
- Use `globalSetup` to create auth state once
- Use `context.route()` to block images/CSS when not needed

---

## 6. Mock APIs for Determinism

Isolate UI tests from backend flakiness.

**DO**:
```typescript
await page.route('**/api/products', route => {
  route.fulfill({ status: 200, body: JSON.stringify([{ id: 1, name: 'Mock' }]) });
});
```

